        </header>


        <!-- REQUIRED FILES -->
        <section id="gridRequired">
            <header class="content-block bg-light-grey">
                <div class="container">
                    <h3>Required files</h3>
                </div>
            </header>
            <div class="content-block">
                <div class="container">
                    <p>SCSS files required: <code>_objects.grid.scss</code></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <header class="content-block bg-light-grey">
            <div class="container">
                <h3>Grid system</h3>
                <p>This grid system uses flexbox and flexbox grid mixins.</p>
                <p>The grid file <code>objects.grid.scss</code> includes 12 column sizes at small, medium and large breakpoints. 2% is the default gutter and can be changed in the grid settings file <code>settings.grid.scss</code></p>
                <p>If you are not using this for your project or require a more simplified version, it may be more beneficial to not include the file and create your own grid system using the <code>objects.grid.scss</code> as a guide as well as any more options from the flexbox grid mixins.</p>
                <p>For more info on how to configure your own grids see the docs <a href="http://thingsym.github.io/flexbox-grid-mixins">here</a></p>
            </div>
        </header>


        <!-- BASIC FLUID GRID -->
        <section id="gridBasic">
            <header class="content-block bg-light-grey">
                <div class="container">
                    <h3>Basic fluid grid</h3>
                    <p>The container requires the class <code>.grid</code> and each grid column requires a class starting with <code>.grid__col-</code> plus the relevant column number width eg. <code>.grid__col-12</code> for full width and <code>.grid__col-6</code> for half width.</p>
                    <p></p>
{{> snippet-grid-basic }}
                </div>
            </header>

